The vz.58 Pistol 556 is manufactured by Czech Small Arms (formerly known as D-Technik) in Jablunka, Czech Republic and includes the following:  two 30 round clear polycarbonate magazines, CD which contains manual and historical information, cleaning kit, and sling. As found with the Czech Small Arms (CSA) line of vz.58 rifles, all vz.58 pistols possess the patented 'push-down' plate on the bolt carrier. The patented ‘push-down’ plate ensures the user will not experience possible misfire problems that can be found with other manufacturer vz.58 type firearms.

Important Notes:  The bayonet lug is not attached to front sight.  Reason:  it is not possible to fix a bayonet to the vz.58 pistol as the proximity of the bayonet lug to the gas adapter/block does not permit attachment.  In addition, CzechPoint is unable to fill requests for the type of front sling swivel, front sight base, and/or trigger guard (rear sling swivel is the same for all vz.58 pistols - as shown in the photo).

The vz.58 Pistol 556 possesses all Czech manufactured original parts (USA made parts to comply with section 922(r) is not a requirement on pistols).  The color of the finish is a matte black coating (cured at 300°F).   The new production pistol barrels are manufactured by Lothar Walther and made from a high alloy Chrome Molybdenum steel (4340) and is chrome-lined.  The bore and chamber are 5.56 NATO spec. The muzzle nut has been threaded onto the barrel threads and has been spot welded at the 6 o'clock position.   The threaded muzzle is 14x1 right hand (standard vz.58 thread pattern). 

The rear sling swivel screw has been spot welded from inside the receiver (weld on sling swivel screw can be removed with rotary tool).   For those that receive an approved BATFE Form 1 SBR (short barreled rifle) for their vz.58, the sling swivel screw can be removed (receiver sling plate is held to the receiver by sling swivel screw).  Once the sling swivel screw and receiver sling plate is removed, any vz.58 stock can be readily attached to the vz.58 receiver.  This is a great 'do-it-yourself' Form 1 SBR.   SBR Warning: a stock can only be legally attached to this pistol after a Form 1 has been approved by BATFE.   Attaching a stock to the vz.58 pistol, without an approved Form 1, is a federal felony and conviction could result in 10 years imprisonment and a $250,000 fine.

Drilled and tapped holes for the receiver side rail ARE included in the purchase price of the pistol. In other words, you can easily install our optional side rail by removing the two screws in the receiver and screw on the side rail with a hex/Allen wrench. GUNSMITHING IS NOT REQUIRED TO ATTACH THE SIDE RAIL TO OUR VZ.58 PISTOL. Do not forget to use high strength thread-locker on the screws while attaching the side rail. To purchase the side rail, please see the vz.58 spare parts section (part no: VZ58-59R) or type VZ58-59R into the 'search' window and click on 'receiver side rail.'

The magwell adapter, to use USGI M16/AR-15 magazines, is sold separately as an accessory and is not included with the purchase price of the pistol. title: For Sale:  [FS] CZ-USA 75D PCR Compact

Nearly identical in size to the CZ 75 Compact, it weighs in at a full 1/4 pound lighter owing to its forged aluminum frame, making it more comfortable for everyday carry. Equipped with a decocking lever, the PCR is designed to be decocked before holstering. After decocking, the trigger safety is much like that of a double action revolver. I have for sale/trade a nice Russian SKS, this particular SKS is somewhat rare and is what is known as a "Letter Gun" or "Letter Series" SKS, Google it to find out if you don't know, but basically it was the last of the SKS's produced by Russia, they are believed to have been made around 1955-1957, this particular one is the "I" model, denoted by the Cyrillic "N" after the last digit of the S/N, there also were "D" and "K" models.

These are also known as "Side Star" SKS's due to the Tula star being on the side.

When I bought it it had a craptastic Tapco stock on it, and a tall as heck scope mount receiver cover. I took all that off(NO LONGER HAVE THE STUFF) and fit it into a Norinco Stock, with the standard Receiver Cover, it's why it has the Spike Bayonet, it is a Russian SKS! I just refinished the Stock and Hand guard as well. Has a cleaning kit in the trapdoor in the buttstock, only thing it's missing is the Cleaning Rod, would make a nice addition to a collection or a nice shooter, it does function FLAWLESSLY, and doesn't slam fire! No ammo is included at this price, and look up the Russian SKS's before you start commenting on my price, they are going for more than $550 everywhere else, these are the best quality SKS that was produced, the milling was fantastic, and it's all milled parts, NO STAMPED!

Only trade I'm looking for is a Taurus PT92 or PT917, and will include ammo if I receive ammo, will match round for round, I have 280 rounds of which 100 is ready to go on 10 round stripper clips.

NO NON FIREARM TRADES!

Located in Sapulpa, PM or Text REDACTED
